  "categories": ["Project Management"],
  "tutorial": "## Jira Cloud OAuth 2.0 Setup\n\n### Creating an Atlassian OAuth 2.0 App\n\n1. Go to [developer.atlassian.com/console/myapps](https://developer.atlassian.com/console/myapps)\n2. Click **Create** > **OAuth 2.0 integration**\n3. Give your app a name and agree to terms\n4. Under **Authorization**, add a callback URL (e.g., `http://localhost:3006/oauth/callback`)\n5. Under **Permissions**, add:\n   - Jira API > `read:jira-work`\n   - Jira API > `write:jira-work`\n   - Jira API > `read:jira-user`\n6. Under **Settings**, copy your **Client ID** and **Client secret**\n\n### OAuth Flow\n\n1. Call `GET /oauth/authorize` to get the authorization URL\n2. User visits the URL and grants permission\n3. Exchange the code via `POST /oauth/callback`\n4. Use the access token with `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n5. The server auto-resolves your Jira Cloud site. If you have multiple sites, use `jira_cloud_list_sites` and `jira_cloud_select_site` to choose one.",
